The ANC’s Treasurer- General, Paul Mashatile has instituted an urgent investigation into a R100 million deal for election posters. The party says in a statement that it was served with an invoice for the 35 000 posters. The ANC says Mashatile was not aware of the transaction until the invoice was brought to his attention. It says since Mashatile had not authorized the procurement – he has instituted the urgent probe. A report will be released when the investigation is completed.  Watch video below: 